### Adding Tauri Commands

1. Add the command handler in `src-tauri/src/commands.rs`:

```rust
#[tauri::command]
pub async fn my_command(arg: String) -> Result<String, AppError> {
    Ok(format!("Received: {}", arg))
    }
    ```

    2. Register the command in `src-tauri/src/lib.rs`:

    ```rust
    .invoke_handler(tauri::generate_handler![
    commands::greet,
    commands::my_command, // Add here
    ])
    ```

    3. Call from frontend in `src/lib/tauri-bridge.ts`:

    ```typescript
    export async function myCommand(arg: string): Promise<string> {
        return invoke<string>("my_command", { arg });
            }
            ```

            ### Building

            #### Development

            ```bash
            make dev
            ```

            This starts the Vite dev server and Tauri in development mode with hot reload.

            #### Production

            ```bash
            make build-release
            ```

            Builds are placed in `src-tauri/target/release/bundle/`.

            ### Generating Icons

            1. Create a 1024x1024 PNG icon
            2. Run: `pnpm tauri icon <path-to-icon.png>`

                ## Configuration

                ### Tauri Configuration

                See `src-tauri/tauri.conf.json` for Tauri settings including:
                - Window dimensions
                - App identifier
                - Bundle settings
                - Security permissions

                ### Capabilities

                Tauri 2.x uses capabilities for security permissions. See `src-tauri/capabilities/default.json`.

